com.igeekinc.indelible.indeliblefs.events

Class IndelibleEventQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.igeekinc.indelible.indeliblefs.events.IndelibleEventQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<IndelibleEvent>, java.lang.Runnable, java.util.Collection<IndelibleEvent>, java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<IndelibleEvent>, java.util.Queue<IndelibleEvent>

    public class IndelibleEventQueue
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable, java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue<IndelibleEvent>
    Takes new events (via IndelibleEventListener) and a historical event source (via IndelibleEventListener) and presents a unified queue of events. Events are taken from the historical source until they catch up with the new events.
    Author:
    David L. Smith-Uchida
